                                     239 *TITLE                                                                  00240021
                                     240 *                                                                       00250021
                                     241 *            'IKFCBL1B'                                                 00260021
                                     242 *                                                                       00270021
                                     243 *STATUS:                                                                00280021
                                     244 *                                                                       00290021
                                     245 *   CHANGE LEVEL 000                                                    00300021
                                     246 *                                                                       00310021
                                     247 *FUNCTION/OPERATION:                                                    00320021
                                     248 *                                                                       00330021
                                     249 *   PHASE 1'S GENERAL FUNCTION:                                         00340021
                                     250 *   ENCODES THE ENTIRE SOURCE PROGRAM INTO INTERNAL COMPILER TEXT.      00350021
                                     251 *   PRODUCES P0 TEXT FROM THE PROCEDURE DIVISION.   PRODUCES OUTPUT     00360021
                                     252 *   LISTING AND/OR A-TEXT LISTING IF AN OBJECT MODULE LISTING IS        00370021
                                     253 *   REQUIRED.   CREATES DICTIONARY ENTRIES FOR PROCEDURE NAMES.         00380021
                                     254 *                                                                       00390021
                                     255 *   THE FUNCTION/OPERATION OF ACCESS:                                   00400021
                                     256 *   CONTROLS ALL REFERENCES TO THE DICTIONARY INCLUDING THE SPILLIN     00410021
                                     257 *   AND RETRIEVING OF SECTIONS OF THE DICTIONARY FROM DISKS, ETC.       00420021
                                     258 *   PHASE 1 USES ACCESS TO MAKE ENTRIES FOR PROCEDURE NAMES.            00430021
                                     259 *                                                                       00440021
                                     260 *ENTRY POINTS:                                                          00450021
                                     261 *                                                                       00460021
                                     262 *      PH1B                                                             00470021
                                     263 *                                                                       00480021
                                     264 *INPUT:                                                                 00490021
                                     265 *                                                                       00500021
                                     266 *        SYSIN - SOURCE PROGRAM (IF NOLIB IN EFFECT)                    00510021
                                     267 *        SYSUT4 - SOURCE PROGRAM (IF LIB IN EFFECT)                     00520021
                                     268 *                                                                       00530021
                                     269 *OUTPUT:                                                                00540021
                                     270 *                                                                       00550021
                                     271 *        SYSUT2  PROC. IC TEXT (P0) AND E TEXT IN PROC. DIV.            00560021
                                     272 *               LISTING A-TEXT.                                         00570021
                                     273 *        SYSPRINT  SOURCE PROGRAM LISTING (IF NOLIB IN EFFECT)          00580021

0                                    274 *                                                                       00590021
                                     275 *EXTERNAL ROUTINES:                                                     00600021
                                     276 *                                                                       00610021
                                     277 *        PHASE 00  LINK TO I-O AND INTERPHASE COMMON REGION             00620021
                                     278 *        PRIME     ASSIGN AN AREA IN A TABLE REGION TO INDIVIDUAL T     00630021
                                     279 *        INSERT    GET ROOM FOR AN ENTRY TO BE MADE IN A TABLE          00640021
                                     280 *        TABREL    RELEASE TABLE, FREE AREA IF NO LONGER NEEDED.        00650021
                                     281 *        STATIC    NOTE NO NEW ENTRY TO BE MADE, RELEASE UNUSED ARE     00660021
                                     282 *                                                                       00670021
                                     283 *EXITS- NORMAL:                                                         00680021
                                     284 *                                                                       00690021
                                     285 *   VIA PHASE 00 TO PHASE 2                                             00700021
                                     286 *                                                                       00710021
                                     287 *   CALLING SEQUENCE:                                                   00720021
                                     288 *   L   JH,COSADR     BALR   0,JH     DC   X'A0'                        00730021
                                     289 *                                                                       00740021
                                     290 *EXITS-ERROR                                                            00750021
                                     291 *                                                                       00760021
                                     292 *   NONE                                                                00770021
                                     293 *                                                                       00780021
                                     294 *TABLES/WORK AREAS COMTBL, QLTABL, APPTBL,PNTABL, PNQTBL, PIOTBL,       00790021
                                     295 *   CKPTBL, OD2TBL, FNTBL, RCDTBL, SPNTBL, RNMTBL, RWRTBL, ROUTBL,      00800021
                                     296 *   DETTBL, DICOT, TOTTBL, UPSTBL.                                      00810021
                                     297 *   148 BYTES ARE RESERVED UNDER R13 AND WORK AREAS START AT DIVCOD     00820021
                                     298 *   PH1B IS PASSED THE P1BTBL WHICH CONTAINS INFORMATION NECESSARY      00830021
                                     299 *   CONTINUE PROCESSING THE SOURCE PROGRAM. IF PH1A HITS EOF ON INP     00840021
                                     300 *   THE  EOPPH1 BIT IN PH1BYTE IN COMMON IS SET ON AND PH1B WILL        00850021
                                     301 *   RELEASE THE APPROPRIATE TABLES AND EXIT TO PHASE 00.                00860021
                                     302 *   TABLES ARE DESCRIBED IN PLM AND LISTING.                            00870021

                                     340 *  13    GLOBAL TABLE BASE, NEVER TOUCHED, ALSO PHASE 1'S BASE REG.     01250021
                                     341 *  14    LINK REGISTER, CALL REGISTER FOR SUBROUTINE                    01260021
                                     342 *  15    BASE REGISTER FOR INTERFACE AND INFREQUENT SUBROUTINES         01270021
                                     343 *                                                                       01280021
                                     344 *   GENERAL CONSIDERATIONS IN ACCESS PROCESSING                         01290021
                                     345 *   ACCESS HANDLES ON ERROR CONDITION, ALMOST NO EXCEPTION - PUT CO     01300021
                                     346 *   IN REGISTER 15.  IF A SUCCESSFUL OUTPUT REGISTER 15 SET TO 0, O     01310021
                                     347 *   WISE SET TO 4 IF NAME IS NOT FOUND, SET TO 8 IF NAME IS DUPLICA     01320021
                                     348 *   DEFINED, SET TO 12 IF NAME REFERENCED BY ACCESS WAS ELEMENTART      01330021
                                     349 *                                                                       01340021
                                     350 *   THE CONVENTION OF HANDLING GOOD OUTPUT, ACCESS ALWAYS USES REG.     01350021
                                     351 *   FOR STARTING ADDRESS OF ENTRY'S ATTRIBUTES, REG. 3 FOR DICTIONA     01360021
                                     352 *   POINTER OF ENTRY, AND REG. 15 SET TO ZERO, REG. 1 CONTAINS THE      01370021
                                     353 *   DICTIONARY POINTER OF THE NEXT ENTRY. REG. 0 AND 1 ARE NOT REST     01380021

                                     484+*    DICTIONARY SEGMENTS.  IT CONTAINS AN ENTRY FOR EACH SECTION AND    12420020
                                     485+*    ITS ORDER CORRESPONDS TO THE ORDER OF THE SECTIONS.                12510020

                                     493+*      AND CORE, ARE TRUE.  AFTER SPILL, UNTIL UPDATE, THE TRUE         13230020

0                                    750+*   ROUTINE 'DHASH'                                                     36360020
                                     751+*       USED BY BOTH 'ENT','L' SERIES                                   36450020
                                     752+*                                                                       36540020
                                     753+*     HASHES BCD NAME, LOCATES CORRES. HASH TABLE ENTRY                 36630020
                                     754+*    INPUT  R9=A(BCD NAME)       'ENT'  R9  'L' R9                      36720020
                                     755+*           R11= BCD NAME CNT            R11     R11                    36810020
                                     756+*    OUTPUT R8= 0,DICT PNTR             R8      R8                      36900020
                                     757+*           R10= A(HASH TABLE ENTRY)     R10     R10                    36990020
                                     758+*           R8/R9  EVEN/ODD  DIVIDEND                                   37080020
                                     759+*           R10/R11  EVEN/ODD  INCREM./COMPAR.                          37170020
                                     760+*                                                                       37260020
                                     761+*    HASHING FUNCTION                                                   37350020
                                     762+*      SEGMENT NAME (INCL. CNT) INTO 4 BYTE LENGTHS, ADD LENGTHS        37440020
                                     763+*      TOGETHER LOGICALLY, DIVIDE SUM BY SIZE OF HASH TABLE, MULT       37530020
                                     764+*      REMAIN. BY 3 TO OBTAIN DISPL. ADD IT TO A(HASH TABLE) AND        37620020
                                     765+*      PICK UP CORRES. ENTRY                                            37710020
                                     766+*      ENTRY=0 OR DICT. PNTR OF LAST BCD NAME WHICH HASHED TO THIS LOC  37800020
                                     767+*                                                                       37890020
                                     768+*     NOTE THAT INPUT NAME IS PADDED OUT WITH ZEROES SO 4 BYTES CAN BE  37980020
                                     769+*     ADDED AT A TIME                                                   38070020
                                     770+*                                                                       38160020
                                     771+*                                                                       38250020
